cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with Multimodal Automatic Speech Recognition, which falls under the domain of natural language processing and speech recognition, making cs.CL the most likely category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper also deals with the visual modality and its integration with speech recognition, which falls under the domain of computer vision, making cs.CV a likely category.
3. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper deals with speech recognition and audio signal processing, which falls under the domain of sound, making cs.SD a likely category.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the performance of different models and their adaptation techniques, which falls under the domain of machine learning, making cs.LG a likely category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the integration of multiple modalities (audio and visual) for speech recognition, which falls under the domain of multimedia, making cs.MM a likely category.
